1
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:43,440
♪I don't want to hear you
nagging nonstop♪

2
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:46,790
♪Can't you just give me the result♪

3
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:49,960
♪Don't think being older
makes you so much greater♪

4
00:00:50,170 --> 00:00:51,710
♪Just bring it on♪

5
00:00:51,910 --> 00:00:53,170
♪Watch how I'll handle you♪

6
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,080
♪Hey, I'll just keep on nagging♪

7
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,010
♪Keep on nagging♪

8
00:00:59,010 --> 00:01:02,030
♪You're annoying; do not get me mad♪

9
00:01:02,030 --> 00:01:05,140
♪I'm always the one
taking the blame for you♪

10
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:08,690
♪Don't be afraid to speak;
I might hold a grudge♪

11
00:01:08,690 --> 00:01:09,970
♪No. 132♪

12
00:01:09,970 --> 00:01:10,910
♪357, what do you want♪

13
00:01:11,110 --> 00:01:12,280
♪Stop right there♪

14
00:01:13,540 --> 00:01:16,900
♪In this noisy, rowdy world,
fate is so amazing♪

15
00:01:17,060 --> 00:01:20,150
♪When we go crazy together,
joy is always with us♪

16
00:01:20,150 --> 00:01:23,260
♪We'll party till dawn♪

17
00:01:23,260 --> 00:01:26,540
♪Laughing, jumping, with no worries♪

18
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:28,060
♪You're clearly so strange♪

19
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:29,580
♪I'm clearly so cute♪

20
00:01:29,580 --> 00:01:32,630
♪Even if they don't get it,
it doesn't matter♪

21
00:01:32,630 --> 00:01:36,330
♪Even if it's always crazy and weird♪

22
00:01:36,330 --> 00:01:39,410
♪I still need fresh reasons for myself♪

23
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:47,070
=Hilarious Family 2=

24
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:50,260
=Episode 11=

25
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:59,300
(Tea)

26
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:05,750
Leisurely drinking Baihe wine.

27
00:02:06,550 --> 00:02:07,700
Whisking all the Suzhou tea.

28
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:10,880
Miss, I've waited for you all morning.

29
00:02:10,950 --> 00:02:11,790
Let's go.

30
00:02:19,390 --> 00:02:20,470
- Let me.
- Thanks.

31
00:02:36,660 --> 00:02:40,340
(Flowers)

32
00:02:41,390 --> 00:02:42,230
Sixi!

33
00:02:42,670 --> 00:02:43,510
Sixi.

34
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:44,670
Sixi!

35
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:45,950
Sir, stop the carriage.

36
00:02:46,510 --> 00:02:47,350
Sixi!

37
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:48,860
Guiwei.

38
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:50,170
What is it?

39
00:02:50,180 --> 00:02:51,790
Sixi, Kan is in trouble.

40
00:02:51,790 --> 00:02:52,770
What happened?

41
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:53,700
He was thrown

42
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:54,640
into jail.

43
00:02:56,470 --> 00:02:57,870
Sir, please tell Yu

44
00:02:57,870 --> 00:02:59,070
I won't go to Suzhou for now.

45
00:02:59,070 --> 00:03:00,050
Sorry to trouble him.

46
00:03:01,510 --> 00:03:02,470
What about your luggage?

47
00:03:02,470 --> 00:03:04,280
Put it at Anping Bridge.

48
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:07,170
Anping Bridge?

49
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:12,500
(Jail)

50
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:16,990
What sin did I commit

51
00:03:16,990 --> 00:03:18,020
in my past life?

52
00:03:18,020 --> 00:03:19,680
Why do I have to meet you guys?

53
00:03:20,230 --> 00:03:21,070
If I don't sell tea,

54
00:03:21,070 --> 00:03:22,170
you will throw me in prison.

55
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:23,610
Fine, I sell tea,

56
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:25,190
but I still end up here with you.

57
00:03:25,190 --> 00:03:26,170
Lower your voice.

58
00:03:27,220 --> 00:03:28,070
Stop posing.

59
00:03:28,070 --> 00:03:29,190
Think of a way.

60
00:03:29,190 --> 00:03:30,170
I'm thinking now.

61
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:33,240
He's here. Be quick.

62
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:35,170
Thanks, Xia.

63
00:03:36,820 --> 00:03:37,800
Sixi.

64
00:03:38,470 --> 00:03:39,470
Guiwei.

65
00:03:39,470 --> 00:03:40,450
Sixi.

66
00:03:40,540 --> 00:03:41,380
Thanks, Advisor Xia.

67
00:03:41,380 --> 00:03:42,370
Are you all right?

68
00:03:43,540 --> 00:03:45,370
I didn't expect things
to turn out like this.

69
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:46,980
Kan,

70
00:03:46,980 --> 00:03:48,120
are you hurt?

71
00:03:48,860 --> 00:03:50,720
Get me out of here.

72
00:03:52,540 --> 00:03:54,210
At least you're not hurt.

73
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:56,890
Guiwei, Guiwei.

74
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:57,910
Kan,

75
00:03:57,910 --> 00:03:58,930
did they torture you?

76
00:04:01,660 --> 00:04:02,640
Alright. Here.

77
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:06,680
There's no food here,

78
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:07,730
so we brought some food.

79
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,140
Come on.

80
00:04:09,140 --> 00:04:10,120
You...

81
00:04:10,660 --> 00:04:11,580
What on earth happened?

82
00:04:11,580 --> 00:04:12,800
How did you get arrested?

83
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,970
A customer reported us
for not having a tea permit.

84
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:16,050
Tea permit?

85
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:17,470
I'm so mad about it.

86
00:04:17,490 --> 00:04:18,540
You don't have a tea permit

87
00:04:18,550 --> 00:04:19,570
before opening a tea shop?

88
00:04:19,870 --> 00:04:20,820
It's so simple.

89
00:04:20,820 --> 00:04:21,810
My fault.

90
00:04:23,670 --> 00:04:24,920
What is a tea permit?

91
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:26,050
Is it important?

92
00:04:26,510 --> 00:04:27,810
Are you serious?

93
00:04:27,890 --> 00:04:29,040
Selling tea without a permit

94
00:04:29,110 --> 00:04:30,650
means you are dealing in illicit tea.

95
00:04:30,820 --> 00:04:32,670
In serious cases,
it means the death penalty.

96
00:04:33,260 --> 00:04:34,240
Death penalty?

97
00:04:36,870 --> 00:04:37,850
Death penalty...

98
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:43,520
Do you not know this?

99
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:45,790
Tea merchants who trade tea

100
00:04:45,790 --> 00:04:46,730
must have a tea permit

101
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:48,250
issued by the government.

102
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:49,410
Why is that?

103
00:04:50,140 --> 00:04:52,150
Tea concerns the state's foundation,

104
00:04:52,150 --> 00:04:54,010
like salt and iron.

105
00:04:54,110 --> 00:04:55,920
It's not something
anyone can sell at will.

106
00:04:56,590 --> 00:04:58,030
I understand salt and iron,

107
00:04:58,030 --> 00:04:59,250
but why tea?

108
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:00,770
You don't get it, do you?

109
00:05:01,310 --> 00:05:03,570
Our state governs
the border through tea.

110
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,670
Those people over there
eat meat and drink dairy.

111
00:05:05,670 --> 00:05:07,340
A day without tea causes stagnation.

112
00:05:07,340 --> 00:05:09,250
Three days without tea causes illness.

113
00:05:09,630 --> 00:05:11,330
Tea is a necessity for them.

114
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:13,400
So, we use tea

115
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:15,130
to trade for their horses.

116
00:05:15,310 --> 00:05:16,290
Horses?

117
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:19,920
Think about it. The main force

118
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:21,890
on the battlefield is cavalry.

119
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:22,910
Without good horses,

120
00:05:22,910 --> 00:05:24,330
how can you beat them?

121
00:05:24,870 --> 00:05:25,990
So, the court always

122
00:05:25,990 --> 00:05:28,450
exchanges tea for horses
and forbids private tea.

123
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:30,650
If private tea ran rampant,

124
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:32,920
they could simply buy it

125
00:05:33,110 --> 00:05:33,990
from you

126
00:05:33,990 --> 00:05:35,040
instead of trading horses.

127
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,820
You would ruin the state's plan.

128
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:39,500
It's serious.

129
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:41,020
Then, let's just get

130
00:05:41,020 --> 00:05:41,860
a tea permit now.

131
00:05:41,860 --> 00:05:42,940
Is that okay?

132
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:45,380
That's easier said than done.

133
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:46,740
Even if you get one now,

134
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:47,700
it's too late.

135
00:05:48,660 --> 00:05:49,980
I think those two

136
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:52,380
will likely be exiled to Shamen Island.

137
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:53,940
What?

138
00:05:53,940 --> 00:05:54,900
Going to that place

139
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,300
is worse than dying.

140
00:05:57,860 --> 00:05:59,420
Is there no way out?

141
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:04,980
Ways depend

142
00:06:05,340 --> 00:06:06,940
on our minds.

143
00:06:10,460 --> 00:06:11,460
Here.

144
00:06:15,060 --> 00:06:16,260
Officials

145
00:06:16,340 --> 00:06:17,820
only investigate reports.

146
00:06:18,340 --> 00:06:19,820
Someone set you up.

147
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:22,420
You mean someone purposely reported us?

148
00:06:23,060 --> 00:06:24,580
That's your claim, not mine.

149
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:26,140
Let's work.

150
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:29,300
I know who did it.

151
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:40,500
Madam, you're so good.

152
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:42,300
With a simple move,

153
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:43,860
you just sent

154
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:44,940
Jing Kan

155
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:46,300
to jail.

156
00:06:48,220 --> 00:06:49,220
Don't think

157
00:06:49,220 --> 00:06:50,460
I'm nice

158
00:06:50,460 --> 00:06:51,540
just because I keep quiet.

159
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:53,500
I'll use this to show him

160
00:06:54,060 --> 00:06:56,300
what I'm capable of.

161
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:57,940
You're right.

162
00:06:58,460 --> 00:07:00,300
Now, the Old Lady isn't home.

163
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:01,820
Everything's in our control.

164
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:06,180
No one would dare to protect him.

165
00:07:07,780 --> 00:07:10,500
Be careful about your words.

166
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:12,620
Eat more if you like,

167
00:07:13,060 --> 00:07:14,140
but don't speak carelessly.

168
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:16,180
If you speak wrongly outside,

169
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:17,920
who'll suffer the consequences?

170
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:19,260
Yes.

171
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:20,460
Yes.

172
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,500
Jing Kan was arrested?

173
00:07:25,260 --> 00:07:27,380
Ms. Luo went too far.

174
00:07:27,540 --> 00:07:28,700
So wicked.

175
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:30,380
We're all family.

176
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,620
A quarrel at home is enough,

177
00:07:32,820 --> 00:07:34,340
but she had him thrown into prison.

178
00:07:34,340 --> 00:07:35,500
Isn't that wicked?

179
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:36,820
Mother,

180
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:38,860
we have no proof now.

181
00:07:38,860 --> 00:07:40,540
How can you be sure it's Auntie?

182
00:07:40,940 --> 00:07:41,860
What do you mean?

183
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:43,140
Are you saying I did it?

184
00:07:43,220 --> 00:07:44,540
What proof do we need?

185
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:46,260
Justice lies in people's hearts.

186
00:07:46,260 --> 00:07:47,220
You know nothing.

187
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:49,100
Auntie,

188
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:50,540
sorry

189
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:51,900
about what we've done before,

190
00:07:52,340 --> 00:07:53,300
but this time,

191
00:07:53,820 --> 00:07:55,420
we really need your help.

192
00:07:55,420 --> 00:07:56,740
Of course.

193
00:07:56,740 --> 00:07:58,700
Jing Kan is

194
00:07:58,700 --> 00:07:59,740
like my own son.

195
00:07:59,740 --> 00:08:01,020
Of course, I'll help.

196
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:02,980
If we help him,

197
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:04,020
what's in it for us?

198
00:08:04,380 --> 00:08:05,340
Go away.

199
00:08:05,660 --> 00:08:07,620
We're family.
What benefit do you expect?

200
00:08:09,180 --> 00:08:10,180
Sixi.

201
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:11,460
Well.

202
00:08:12,060 --> 00:08:13,420
If you ask me

203
00:08:13,420 --> 00:08:15,260
to sew a quilt or make some clothes

204
00:08:15,380 --> 00:08:16,580
for Jing Kan,

205
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:19,260
I can surely do that.

206
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:21,580
But if it involves the government,

207
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,960
I really have no connections.

208
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:25,540
Auntie,

209
00:08:25,820 --> 00:08:26,860
as long as you

210
00:08:26,860 --> 00:08:28,020
can save Jing Kan this time,

211
00:08:28,380 --> 00:08:29,800
I'll agree to any condition you ask.

212
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:31,300
You said it.

213
00:08:31,860 --> 00:08:33,060
If I can rescue him,

214
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:35,460
you'll give me your shop.

215
00:08:35,460 --> 00:08:36,420
Fine.

216
00:08:37,620 --> 00:08:38,580
What plan do you have?

217
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:40,500
My uncle...

218
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,580
Just shut up.

219
00:08:42,580 --> 00:08:43,540
Such nonsense.

220
00:08:43,780 --> 00:08:45,060
My uncle can save Jing Kan.

221
00:08:45,140 --> 00:08:46,300
He can't.

222
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:49,660
Her uncle used to work
for the Patrol Division,

223
00:08:49,660 --> 00:08:51,300
but now he's been dismissed.

224
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:53,820
Zhenzhu doesn't know this.

225
00:08:53,940 --> 00:08:56,220
If there's anything I can do,

226
00:08:56,620 --> 00:08:58,460
I'll surely help you.

227
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:04,340
What to do then?

228
00:09:06,660 --> 00:09:07,660
What to do?

229
00:09:09,060 --> 00:09:10,980
Have you told your Mother about this?

230
00:09:11,780 --> 00:09:12,780
Not yet.

231
00:09:13,580 --> 00:09:14,540
Go tell her then.

232
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:15,740
Let me tell you.

233
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:17,680
Only the person who tied the knot
can untie it.

234
00:09:18,060 --> 00:09:19,700
Yes, I understand that.

235
00:09:20,860 --> 00:09:22,940
I'm just afraid
she won't spare Jing Kan.

236
00:09:23,260 --> 00:09:25,140
Why don't I go to Auntie first?

237
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:25,980
Go away.

238
00:09:25,980 --> 00:09:27,340
Go take some

239
00:09:27,380 --> 00:09:29,220
lily and lotus seed congee,

240
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:30,820
so Sixi can relax.

241
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:31,900
No need.

242
00:09:32,660 --> 00:09:33,740
I won't drink the congee.

243
00:09:35,420 --> 00:09:36,260
I'm leaving.

244
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:37,540
You're not going to drink?

245
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:39,980
Take care of your health.

246
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:41,420
Don't get worked up.

247
00:09:45,660 --> 00:09:46,660
Mother,

248
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:48,340
are we really going to do nothing?

249
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:49,660
Do what?

250
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:50,940
You two

251
00:09:50,940 --> 00:09:52,420
act like fools.

252
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:55,740
Given the current situation,

253
00:09:55,740 --> 00:09:57,220
Luo Zhusi is clearly set

254
00:09:57,580 --> 00:09:59,100
on punishing Jing Kan.

255
00:09:59,380 --> 00:10:00,940
If you ask me,

256
00:10:00,940 --> 00:10:02,220
Jing Kan needs to take a fall.

257
00:10:02,220 --> 00:10:03,220
Do you think

258
00:10:03,340 --> 00:10:04,580
he respects me in daily life?

259
00:10:05,020 --> 00:10:07,540
Now, he lets his wife come
and plead with me.

260
00:10:08,340 --> 00:10:11,060
Am I someone merciful?

261
00:10:12,580 --> 00:10:14,660
Hasn't your age

262
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:16,580
taught you anything, Mother?

263
00:10:16,580 --> 00:10:18,060
Do you think your face

264
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:19,340
will buy you anything?

265
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:21,260
What good is that for?

266
00:10:21,260 --> 00:10:22,900
If you don't take over the shop now,

267
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:24,900
what if Luo Zhusi takes it away?

268
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:26,780
Here comes the shop again.

269
00:10:26,780 --> 00:10:27,860
Can you really manage it?

270
00:10:28,140 --> 00:10:29,160
That shop is a trap,

271
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:30,580
and you want to jump right into it.

272
00:10:30,580 --> 00:10:31,460
I've eaten more salt

273
00:10:31,460 --> 00:10:32,860
than the rice in your life.

274
00:10:33,020 --> 00:10:34,340
Just cut down on the salt.

275
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:35,580
Aren't you troubled by it?

276
00:10:36,060 --> 00:10:37,460
Let me tell you both.

277
00:10:37,820 --> 00:10:39,940
Do not meddle in this matter now.

278
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:41,340
Whoever goes will be troubled.

279
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:43,020
From my years

280
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:44,580
in this family,

281
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:48,180
we should wait
until Luo Zhusi cools off,

282
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,220
then go with the flow

283
00:10:51,580 --> 00:10:53,340
and find a way to rescue Jing Kan.

284
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:55,860
At the same time,

285
00:10:55,980 --> 00:10:58,740
we can take over that shop.

286
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:02,900
Mother, you're so clever.

287
00:11:04,060 --> 00:11:06,300
You're such a craftswoman,

288
00:11:06,860 --> 00:11:08,980
good at weaving bamboo baskets

289
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:11,220
for drawing water.

290
00:11:11,220 --> 00:11:12,980
You'll surely end up with nothing.

